msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:591
msgid ""
":doc:`MongoDB Enterprise for Windows </tutorial/install-mongodb-"
"enterprise-on-windows>` is now available. It includes support for "
"Kerberos, SSL, and SNMP."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:595 ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:620
msgid ""
"MongoDB Enterprise for Windows does **not** include LDAP support for "
"authentication. However, MongoDB Enterprise for Linux supports using LDAP"
" authentication with an ActiveDirectory server."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:599
msgid "MongoDB Enterprise for Windows includes OpenSSL version 1.0.1g."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:602
msgid "Auditing"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:604
msgid ""
"MongoDB Enterprise adds :doc:`auditing </core/auditing>` capability for "
":binary:`~bin.mongod` and :binary:`~bin.mongos` instances. See "
":ref:`auditing` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:611
msgid "LDAP Support for Authentication"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:613
msgid ""
"MongoDB Enterprise provides support for proxy authentication of users. "
"This allows administrators to configure a MongoDB cluster to authenticate"
" users by proxying authentication requests to a specified Lightweight "
"Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) service. See :doc:`/tutorial/configure-"
"ldap-sasl-openldap` and :doc:`/tutorial/configure-ldap-sasl-"
"activedirectory` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:624
msgid ""
"MongoDB does **not** support LDAP authentication in mixed sharded cluster"
" deployments that contain both version 2.4 and version 2.6 shards. See "
":doc:`/release-notes/2.6-upgrade` for upgrade instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:629
msgid "Expanded SNMP Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/2.6.txt:631
msgid ""
"MongoDB Enterprise has greatly expanded its SNMP support to provide SNMP "
"access to nearly the full range of metrics provided by "
":method:`db.serverStatus()`."
